{'id': 2016016662617, 'title': 'Handmade Lokta Paper Journal Floral Asian Inspired Cover - Blue / Gold', 'handle': 'copy-of-handmade-paper-photo-album-journal-small-jewel-aqua-blue-2', 'description': '

{'id': 2164720205913, 'title': 'Hemp Bag', 'handle': 'hemp-bag-2', 'description': 'Hemp backpacks are made up of from the mixture hemp and cotton. The Hemp Backpack is handmade.
These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.
Hemp Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp yarns.
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
The hemp fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang, and Rolpa.
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using soap or dishwashing detergent
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.
Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.
Do not use any washing machines for hemp bags that you use for other washing materials.', 'published_at': '2019-08-26T15:10:16-05:00', 'created_at': '2019-08-26T15:22:13-05:00', 'vendor': 'Amadara', {'id': 2164799111257, 'title': 'Hemp BackPack', 'handle': 'hemp-backpack-2', 'description': 'Hemp backpacks are made from hemp and cotton it is handmade.
These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.
Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp fibers turned into yarns.
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
Fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang,Rolpa
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using just a bit of wool lite soap.
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.

Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.
Do not use any washing machines for hemp bags that you use for other washing materials.

Size: 17 x 11 x 5 inch (Height x Length x Width) approximate
Weight: 1 Lbs
Material: hemp and cotton
Inside: Single with laptop compartment with velcro
Outside: most have 2-4 front pockets and 2 side water bottle holder pockets as shown in the picture

Some items described as\xa0Tibetan\xa0Silver Are\xa0are cast iron that has been plated with the\xa0silver-colored metal. Most\xa0Tibetan Silver\xa0is copper with tin rather than copper with nickel because nickel causes skin reactions in many people

These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.
Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp fibers turned into yarns.
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
Fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang,Rolpa
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using just a bit of wool lite soap.
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.

Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.
Do not use any washing machines for hemp bags that you use for other washing materials.

{'id': 2166287990873, 'title': 'Handmade Mulberry Paper Hanging Lantern - Batik Design', 'handle': 'handmade-mulberry-paper-hanging-lantern-batik-design-2', 'description': '

Handmade hanging paper lantern gives off a soft, diffused light. It provides a wonderful ambient lighting. This paper was handcrafted from the bark of mulberry tree.They stripped out the bark, dried it in the sun, and then boiled it to soften the pulp. The tender pulp was then mixed with water in a large vat.
The artisans submerged a mesh wire screen into a vat to collect the pulp onto the mesh wire to make a sheet of paper. Then the screen was pressed and dried in the sun. After the paper had completely dried, the sheet of paper can be easily peeled off from the screen. This design used a batik technique or tye dye by using wax and paint to create beautiful abstract designs.
These papers are then transformed into beautiful lanterns. Electrical cord is not included.We recommend you use 40 watts or lower, or fluorescent light bulb.The light bulb needs to hang directly in the center of the lantern, not touching the paper lantern.Earth Friendly and Acid Free Paper.

{'id': 2164803272793, 'title': 'Hemp Backpack', 'handle': 'hemp-backpack-3', 'description': 'Hemp backpacks are made up of from the mixture hemp and cotton. The Hemp Backpack is handmade.\xa0
These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.\xa0
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.\xa0
Hemp Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp yarns.\xa0
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.\xa0
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
The hemp fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang, and Rolpa.
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.\xa0
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using soap or dishwashing detergent\xa0
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.
Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.
Do not use any washing machines for hemp bags that you use for other washing materials.', 'published_at': '2019-08-26T16:23:06-05:00', 'created_at': '2019-08-26T16:27:03-05:00', 'vendor': 'Amadara', The mystique singing bowl is a ritual object used by enlightened Lamas and Tibetan monks in the Himalayan region (Tibet and Nepal) since ancient times. When "played" with a wooden stick, the metal bowl emits resounding and serene sounds. The pitch of the bowl depends on its thickness, size and weight. The smaller bowls produce delicate, high pitch, entrancing sound. The larger bowls produce deeper, full-bodied sounds. Singing bowls create a range of different calming sounds and overtones.

A singing bowl is a perfect tool for meditation, stress reduction and holistic healing. Our singing bowls are handcrafted by local artisans in Nepal. Amadara offers singing bowls in various sizes and designs. To produce a sound, put the singing bowl on the palm of your hand. Strike on the rim and rub the rim in a clockwise motion slowly. This excitation causes the sides and rim of the bowl to vibrate, producing a rich sound. The set includes the singing bowl, a wooden striker and a hand sewn cushion.

Diameter:\xa03\xa01/2"\xa0

{'id': 2166268133465, 'title': 'Handmade Mulberry Paper Hanging Lantern - Batik Design', 'handle': 'handmade-mulberry-paper-hanging-lantern-batik-design', 'description': '

Handmade hanging paper lantern gives off a soft, diffused light. It provides a wonderful ambient lighting. This paper was handcrafted from the bark of mulberry tree.They stripped out the bark, dried it in the sun, and then boiled it to soften the pulp. The tender pulp was then mixed with water in a large vat.
The artisans submerged a mesh wire screen into a vat to collect the pulp onto the mesh wire to make a sheet of paper. Then the screen was pressed and dried in the sun. After the paper had completely dried, the sheet of paper can be easily peeled off from the screen. This design used a batik technique or tye dye by using wax and paint to create beautiful abstract designs.
These papers are then transformed into beautiful lanterns. Electrical cord is not included.We recommend you use 40 watts or lower, or fluorescent light bulb.The light bulb needs to hang directly in the center of the lantern, not touching the paper lantern.Earth Friendly and Acid Free Paper.

\n

Chhepu is one among the three brothers Garuda, Chhepu and Hitimanga. It is told that once the mother of these brothers,requested her husband to give birth of such a son who would be the bravest, most truthful and entitled with all superior marks. Her husband told her to wait for a certain period. She being impatience to wait for a long period, looked the nest whether he was born or not. She found Chhepu in a prematured condition only with formation of head.

It is also told that Chhepu disappeared from the world as he did not want to see the kaliyuga, the great yuga, when the evil would completely trumphant over the good and the world would be destroyed by Vishnu in his incarnation as kalki, the destroyer. Knowing his bravery, truthfulness and entitled with all the superior marks Manjushree wanted to see him and requested Chhepu to show his full form. Chhepu appeared slowly amidst the cloud. Manjushree, as an veteran artist, immediately drew his form by his foot secretly without the knowledge of Cheepu. When Manjushree could finish to draw his head only Chhepu came to know Manjushree\'s deception and immediately disappeared. Due to his bravery, truthfulness and all superior marks, he was given the place at the top of the main entrance of the shrines for the protection from all the dangers. Nagas are the food of Chhepu.

These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.
Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp fibers turned into yarns.
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
Fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang,Rolpa
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using just a bit of wool lite soap.
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.

Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.
Do not use any washing machines for hemp bags that you use for other washing materials.

{'id': 2166300180569, 'title': 'Handmade Mulberry Paper Hanging Lantern - Batik Design', 'handle': 'handmade-mulberry-paper-hanging-lantern-batik-design-5', 'description': '

Handmade hanging paper lantern gives off a soft, diffused light. It provides a wonderful ambient lighting. This paper was handcrafted from the bark of mulberry tree.They stripped out the bark, dried it in the sun, and then boiled it to soften the pulp. The tender pulp was then mixed with water in a large vat.
The artisans submerged a mesh wire screen into a vat to collect the pulp onto the mesh wire to make a sheet of paper. Then the screen was pressed and dried in the sun. After the paper had completely dried, the sheet of paper can be easily peeled off from the screen. This design used a batik technique or tye dye by using wax and paint to create beautiful abstract designs.
These papers are then transformed into beautiful lanterns. Electrical cord is not included.We recommend you use 40 watts or lower, or fluorescent light bulb.The light bulb needs to hang directly in the center of the lantern, not touching the paper lantern.Earth Friendly and Acid Free Paper.

The mystique singing bowl is a ritual object used by enlightened Lamas and Tibetan monks in the Himalayan region (Tibet and Nepal) since ancient times. When "played" with a wooden stick, the metal bowl emits resounding and serene sounds. The pitch of the bowl depends on its thickness, size and weight. The smaller bowls produce delicate, high pitch, entrancing sound. The larger bowls produce deeper, full-bodied sounds. Singing bowls create a range of different calming sounds and overtones.

A singing bowl is a perfect tool for meditation, stress reduction and holistic healing. Our singing bowls are handcrafted by local artisans in Nepal. Amadara offers singing bowls in various sizes and designs. To produce a sound, put the singing bowl on the palm of your hand. Strike on the rim and rub the rim in a clockwise motion slowly. This excitation causes the sides and rim of the bowl to vibrate, producing a rich sound. The set includes the singing bowl, a wooden striker and a hand sewn cushion.

Diameter: 4 1/2"

Design: Thunderbolt / Double Vajra

All measurements are approximate and may vary slightly due to the handmade nature. Like human beings, each piece is unique and beautiful.

{'id': 2164742783065, 'title': 'Hemp Bag', 'handle': 'hemp-bag-4', 'description': '
Hemp backpacks are made up of from the mixture hemp and cotton. The Hemp Backpack is handmade.
These bags are made using natural and organic hemp which are extracted from the cannabis plants from Nepal.
Almost everyone uses a backpack for carrying their valuable items.
Hemp Backpacks are usually made up of strong and durable natural hemp yarns.
The fiber is extracted from the cannabis plant that grows at a height of 20 feet tall.
The stems of the plant are soaked in water for twenty days.
Then the stems are separated from the plant and are boiled in ash water.
The hemp fibers are collected from mainly western part of Nepal like Bajura, Bajhang, and Rolpa.
Hemp fibers are one of the strongest fibers ever found. These fibers are also known for their strength and durability.
The materials that are made from hemp also doesn’t stretch.
The bags can easily be hand-washed in the home using soap or dishwashing detergent
Do not use dishwashing detergent powder as it may contain some chemical not suitable for the hemp bags.
Some of the tips for washing Hemp Bags are as follows:
Slowly soak the hemp bag in a hot water for 15 minutes.
You can also soak the bag in vinegar if possible.
Rinse well by hand and wash the bag using organic soap or a detergent powder.
Dry the hemp bag for a few hours. Remember, the bag dries very quickly.

The mystique singing bowl is a ritual object used by enlightened Lamas and Tibetan monks in the Himalayan region (Tibet and Nepal) since ancient times. When "played" with a wooden stick, the metal bowl emits resounding and serene sounds. The pitch of the bowl depends on its thickness, size and weight. The smaller bowls produce delicate, high pitch, entrancing sound. The larger bowls produce deeper, full-bodied sounds. Singing bowls create a range of different calming sounds and overtones.

A singing bowl is a perfect tool for meditation, stress reduction and holistic healing. Our singing bowls are handcrafted by local artisans in Nepal. Amadara offers singing bowls in various sizes and designs. To produce a sound, put the singing bowl on the palm of your hand. Strike on the rim and rub the rim in a clockwise motion slowly. This excitation causes the sides and rim of the bowl to vibrate, producing a rich sound. The set includes the singing bowl, a wooden striker and a hand sewn cushion.

A singing bowl is a perfect tool for meditation, stress reduction and holistic healing. Our singing bowls are handcrafted by local artisans in Nepal. Amadara offers singing bowls in various sizes and designs. To produce a sound, put the singing bowl on the palm of your hand. Strike on the rim and rub the rim in a clockwise motion slowly. {'id': 2166288416857, 'title': 'Handmade Mulberry Paper Hanging Lantern - Batik Design', 'handle': 'handmade-mulberry-paper-hanging-lantern-batik-design-3', 'description': '

Handmade hanging paper lantern gives off a soft, diffused light. It provides a wonderful ambient lighting. This paper was handcrafted from the bark of mulberry tree.They stripped out the bark, dried it in the sun, and then boiled it to soften the pulp. The tender pulp was then mixed with water in a large vat.
The artisans submerged a mesh wire screen into a vat to collect the pulp onto the mesh wire to make a sheet of paper. Then the screen was pressed and dried in the sun. After the paper had completely dried, the sheet of paper can be easily peeled off from the screen. This design used a batik technique or tye dye by using wax and paint to create beautiful abstract designs.
These papers are then transformed into beautiful lanterns. Electrical cord is not included.We recommend you use 40 watts or lower, or fluorescent light bulb.The light bulb needs to hang directly in the center of the lantern, not touching the paper lantern.Earth Friendly and Acid Free Paper.
